dataLineage.statement:
Layer was downloaded as a shapefile by ITOS from an email from the IMO. It was then analyzed by ITOS for errors. Those errors were corrected and then the layer was sent back to UNOCHA as a feature class within a file database.
The following errors were found and fixed by ITOS: 1. Created and populated admin 0 name and p-code fields 2. Created and populated reference name fields 3. Admin 3 names were repopulated using the Admin3 names from the PP layer 4. Leading space removed from Admin3 name " Aazouniye". 5. Admin3 layer's 66 "litige" records changed to "Litige" 6. 6 records changed in Admin3 layer from all lower case to Proper Case 7.The 16 separate instances of duplicate Admin3 p-codes in the Admin3 layer have been merged into multi-part polygons, with the exception of the duplicate records for 'Litige' in the Admin2 unit of Chouf. 8. Dibbiye was merged into a single polygon, thus removing the shared border. 9. Corrected geometric nesting errors between admin layers
The following errors were found by ITOS but left in candidate: 1. Admin3 layer contains characters "(", ")" and "," which may indicate presence of alternate names. 2. There are 66 'Litige' records throughout the Admin3 layer and we do not believe they refer to an actual named Admin unit, but rather a generic term for a type of area - maybe something like "Disputed" since Litige translates to litigation in French and Lebanon was once a colony of France. 3. The Admin3 p-codes in the Admin3 layer do not build off of the Admin1 and Admin2 p-codes and they are numeric instead of alphanumeric. IMO has instructed ITOS to leave p-codes as is
